/*************************************
    Package.json
*************************************/
> About Application
> Version
> Dependency mang
> Start Script

/*************************************
    Steps To create package.json
*************************************/
> Go inside folder using terminal/cmd
> npm init
> Answer all questions
> type 'yes'


/*************************************
   Dependency In React
*************************************/
> Local Dependency=> Local to folder
> Global Dependency=> local to system
    help to build/create/start/moniter

/*************************************
  Step To local Dependency
*************************************/
> Go inside folder using terminal/cmd
> npm install <package name>/npm i <package name>
  Example > npm install @aakashdeveloper/create-node-app

/*************************************
  Step To Global Dependency
*************************************/
window => Run cmd as admin
mac/linux=> use 'sudo' before command
> Go inside folder using terminal/cmd
> npm install -g <package name>/npm i -g <package name>

  Example > npm install -g create-react-app

/*************************************
  Step To Create React App
*************************************/
Note: You must have create-react-app globally with You 
if not:
> npm install -g create-react-app
> Go inside folder using terminal/cmd
> create-react-app firstapp
> cd firstapp
> npm start
> In browser > http://localhost:3000/

/*************************************
  Files Explain
*************************************/
ReadMe        => Provide information of Application 
package.json  => Contain start command/Dependency/information of app
.gitignore    => Things you dont want to push
src           => All App Development happne here
public        => Static files css/js/images/assets
node_modules  => all node modules here

/*************************************
        Component in React
*************************************/
Functional              |    Class Base
--------------------------------------
Light in weight         |   Heavy as compare to functional 
Cannot handle State     |   Can handle State
Display or render data  |   Logic and render both
Normal Es6 Function     |   Use Class to Create Component

----------------------------------------------
// ES5(Ecma Script)
function add(a,b){
    return a+b
}

// Es6
>>> const add = (a,b) => { return a+b }

add(1,2)

>>> class add {}

